
[1]levite

   LE'VITE, n. [from Levi, one the sons of Jacob.]

   One of the tribe or family of Levi; a descendant of Levi; more
   particularly, an officer in the Jewish church, who was employed in
   manual service, as in bringing wood and other necessaries for the
   sacrifices. The Levites also sung and played on instruments of music.
   They were subordinate to the priests, the descendants of Aaron, who was
   also of the family of Levi.
